snippet.textDisplay:
Tesla Killer? This car is literally the least efficient EV on the market. I'm not even kidding, it has the worse per mile efficiency out of any other EV on the market. 200 mile EPA with a 90 KWH battery, that's awful. And yet it's still slower than a Model S performance LOL. It's heavier, slower, less efficient, lower ranged, and more expensive... OH and it's less safe too.

This car is a prime example of how much farther ahead Tesla is. All of the traditional car manufacturers need to wake up or they're going to lose sales HARD within the next 15 years. And I mean all of them, I'm not just picking on Porsche here, Tesla has been investing in EVs hard and their battery and motor technology is much farther ahead than anyone else
